-- EPS in the First Quarter of ’13 for S&P 500 Stocks by Sectors
-- B y   W e n d y   S o o n g
-- 2013-06-12T20:37:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-12/eps-in-the-first-quarter-of-13-for-s-p-500-stocks-by-sectors.html
Here are the cumulative earnings per share
results for the first quarter of 2013 for  Standard & Poor’s (SPX)  500
Index stocks, broken down into ten sectors: consumer discretionary,
consumer staples, energy, financial, health care, industrials, information
technology, materials, telecommunication services and utilities. Within
sectors, the companies are ranked by year-over-year percent changes.  Profit figures are based on income from continuing operations
excluding some gains and losses. Industry averages are  share-weighted 
percentage changes of year-over-year comparisons.  Earnings estimates  are
provided by Bloomberg.  
